                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="422400" author="yujian" created="Thu, 25 Jul 2024 23:14:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same failure occurred on SLES 15 SP6 client with kernel 6.4.0-150600.23.14-default:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/d1810055-0e97-4509-a93b-58834a4ad5a5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/d1810055-0e97-4509-a93b-58834a4ad5a5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="350518" author="adilger" created="Fri, 21 Oct 2022 19:40:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16258&quot; title=&quot;Explicitly support .splice_write&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16258&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16258&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="350517" author="adilger" created="Fri, 21 Oct 2022 19:40:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/48928&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/48928&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16258&quot; title=&quot;Explicitly support .splice_write&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16258&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16258&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: Explicitly support .splice_write&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; has fixed this problem for Ubuntu22.04, since that patch and the one based on top if it have both passed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/46663bdd-3ad0-4af3-8147-5057ac38898a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/46663bdd-3ad0-4af3-8147-5057ac38898a&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/5cda616c-c670-4721-9eb4-0b03b733aa94&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/5cda616c-c670-4721-9eb4-0b03b733aa94&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No other Ubuntu22.04 test runs have passed in the past 4 weeks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="350070" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2022 23:29:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch:&lt;/del&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/48912&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/48912&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16020&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_244a: FAIL: sendfile+grouplock failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16020&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16020&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: add sanity/244a to always_except&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;Branch: master&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;Current Patch Set: 1&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;del&gt;Commit: 8790cba5ee0facefd24a64862cd8619f432912c8&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="349557" author="adilger" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2022 20:43:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that is definitely a way forward, and will at least avoid new regressions.  We just need to remember to actually fix the problem and remove the subtest from ALWAYS_EXCEPT, as we normally do with similar issues... &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the check needs to be for the kernel version, and not the distro, since the same issue was also hit on el9. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="349535" author="pjones" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2022 16:07:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could we add this test to always_accept while we&apos;re working on a fix and then enforce testing on ubuntu 22.04 immediately to stop any other regressions creeping in?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="347884" author="adilger" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2022 12:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is mostly failing on ubuntu2204, but there was also a failure on RHEL9.0 so it looks like it is a &quot;new kernel&quot; issue related to sendfile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
